title: Vermont Center for Geographic Information, Census Tract Boundaries and Stats, Vermont, 1990
name: Vermont Center for Geographic Information, Census Tract Boundaries and Stats, Vermont, 1990
description:
The 1990 Census TIGER/Line File is an extract of selected geographic and cartographic information from the Census Bureau's TIGER
      (Topologically Integrated Geographic Encoding & Referencing) database.  The primary
      sources of the geographic data base were the USGS RF 100,000 scale maps from photographically reduced (to RF 100,000 scale) and
      mosaicked RF 24,000 scale maps.  The attribute source is the 1990 Population & Housing Census, Summary Tape
      File (STF) 3.
Please search for Vermont-GIS for more   local level GIS datasets.
